the apache  license for details see our site policies java is a registered trademark of oracle andor its affiliates last updated february   send feedback about this page documentation feedback freebase api deprecated product feedback cancel cobham plc  wikipedia cobham plc from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from flight refuelling limited jump to navigation search cobham plc type public traded as lse cob industry aerospace defence founded  headquarters wimborne minster england uk key people mike wareing chairman david lockwood ceo revenue £ million  operating income £ million  net income £ million  website wwwcobhamcom cobham plc is a british manufacturing company based in wimborne minster dorset england it is listed on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index according to defense news it is the st largest defence firm in the world and the fifth largest in the uk based on  revenue contents  history  operations  products  queens awards for enterprise  sports club  see also  references  external links historyedit cobham was founded as flight refuelling limited frl at raf ford in sussex by sir alan cobham in  it moved to tarrant rushton in dorset in  it developed the probe and drogue method of airtoair refuelling in  and michael cobham took over the leadership of the business from his father in  in september  it acquired ml aviation for £ million which had taken over nash  thompson a major competitor the previous year in early  cobham purchased stec corporation maker of general aviation autopilots for  million and in february  cobham bought the sensor and antenna systems division of bae systems for  million then in june  cobham acquired sparta inc a us defence business for  million it was renamed cobham analytic solutions in september  cobham completed the purchase of the radio frequency components business of macom for  million in april  cobham agreed to purchase argotek inc a provider of highend information assurance services to the united states intelligence community for  million then in june  a cobham – northrop grumman – joint venture won the us armys us billion competition to supply vehicular intercom systems in october  cobham analytic solutions was sold for  million to the privately owned parsons corporation then in june  cobham acquired danish satellite communications company thrane  thrane as making it the core of cobhams new satcom strategic business unit sbu to include seatel marine tracstar land and omnipless airborne satcom product lines in may  cobham acquired antenna systems business axell wireless in july  cobham bought out fb heliservices joint venture partner bristow helicopters in april  cobham sold chelton flight systems and stec corporation to genesys aerosystems then in may  cobham acquired wireless communications company aeroflex holding corporation for  billion in august  david lockwood was named ceo replacing bob murphy operationsedit cobham falcon about to touch down cobham is organised into three technology divisions mission systems defence systems and aerospace  surveillance the cobham mission systems division claims to be the world market leader in aerial refuelling the cobham defence systems division specialises in radar communication and electronic warfare systems and claims to be the world leader in advanced tactical military vehicle intercom systems the cobham aerospace and security division provides a range of electronic products for airborne marine and land applications cobham aviation services part of cobham mission systems operates more than  fixed and rotary wing aircraft around the world it specialises in the conversion and support of a wide range of civil and military aircraft and through an fb heliservices consortium with bristow helicopters at the uks defence helicopter flying school trains all uk helicopter pilots for the royal navy royal air force and british army productsedit carleton life support a subsidiary of cobham based in davenport iowa makes the mk  rebreather used by the united states navy the company produces the guardian st a batteryoperated tracing device used by the american fbi the device is secured under a car by a strong magnet it is only available to law enforcement agencies in his  book data and goliath american security expert bruce schneier wrote that cobham sells a system enabling buyers to send blind calls to mobile phones calls that dont ring and are undetectable by the recipient as described by schneier the blind call allows the sender to track the phones location to within one metre schneier noted that cobhams customers include the governments of algeria brunei ghana pakistan saudi arabia singapore and the united states queens awards for enterpriseedit  cobham surveillance based in segensworth hampshire england received a queens award for enterprise in the international trade category the business – formerly known as domo ltd – tripled its export sales in three years  cobham surveillance based in segensworth hampshire received a queens award for enterprise in the innovation category the award was for the development of its solo wireless digital audio and video link technology that improves safety for bomb disposal teams and law enforcement personnel by increasing the range at which they can effectively operate their robotic bomb disposal equipment  cobham antenna systems based in marlow buckinghamshire received a queens award for enterprise in the international trade category the business – formerly known as chelton ltd – continuously increased export revenues over six years and sells over  of its production overseas sports clubedit the company created cobham sports and social club a members club in merley near the main manufacturing site in wimborne dorset which is used as the ground for merley cobham sports fc see alsoedit companies portal aerospace industry in the united kingdom cobham aviation services australia sargent fletcher cobham technical services  era technology ltd ref