 michael cobham took over the leadership of the business from his father in  in september  it acquired ml aviation for £ million which had taken over nash  thompson a major competitor the previous year in early  cobham purchased stec corporation maker of general aviation autopilots for  million and in february  cobham bought the sensor and antenna systems division of bae systems for  million then in june  cobham acquired sparta inc a us defence business for  million it was renamed cobham analytic solutions in september  cobham completed the purchase of the radio frequency components business of macom for  million in april  cobham agreed to purchase argotek inc a provider of highend information assurance services to the united states intelligence community for  million then in june  a cobham – northrop grumman – joint venture won the us armys us billion competition to supply vehicular intercom systems in october  cobham analytic solutions was sold for  million to the privately owned parsons corporation then in june  cobham acquired danish satellite communications company thrane  thrane as making it the core of cobhams new satcom strategic business unit sbu to include seatel marine tracstar land and omnipless airborne satcom product lines in may  cobham acquired antenna systems business axell wireless in july  cobham bought out fb heliservices joint venture partner bristow helicopters in april  cobham sold chelton flight systems and stec corporation to genesys aerosystems then in may  cobham acquired wireless communications company aeroflex holding corporation for  billion in august  david lockwood was named ceo replacing bob murphy operationsedit cobham falcon about to touch down cobham is organised into three technology divisions mission systems defence systems and aerospace  surveillance the cobham mission systems division claims to be the world market leader in aerial refuelling the cobham defence systems division specialises in radar communication and electronic warfare systems and claims to be the world leader in advanced tactical military vehicle intercom systems the cobham aerospace and security division provides a range of electronic products for airborne marine and land applications cobham aviation services part of cobham mission systems operates more than  fixed and rotary wing aircraft around the world it specialises in the conversion and support of a wide range of civil and military aircraft and through an fb heliservices consortium with bristow helicopters at the uks defence helicopter flying school trains all uk helicopter pilots for the royal navy royal air force and british army productsedit carleton life support a subsidiary of cobham based in davenport iowa makes the mk  rebreather used by the united states navy the company produces the guardian st a batteryoperated tracing device used by the american fbi the device is secured under a car by a strong magnet it is only available to law enforcement agencies in his  book data and goliath american security expert bruce schneier wrote that cobham sells a system enabling buyers to send blind calls to mobile phones calls that dont ring and are undetectable by the recipient as described by schneier the blind call allows the sender to track the phones location to within one metre schneier noted that cobhams customers include the governments of algeria brunei ghana pakistan saudi arabia singapore and the united states queens awards for enterpriseedit  cobham surveillance based in segensworth hampshire england received a queens award for enterprise in the international trade category the business – formerly known as domo ltd – tripled its export sales in three years  cobham surveillance based in segensworth hampshire received a queens award for enterprise in the innovation category the award was for the development of its solo wireless digital audio and video link technology that improves safety for bomb disposal teams and law enforcement personnel by increasing the range at which they can effectively operate their robotic bomb disposal equipment  cobham antenna systems based in marlow buckinghamshire received a queens award for enterprise in the international trade category the business – formerly known as chelton ltd – continuously increased export revenues over six years and sells over  of its production overseas sports clubedit the company created cobham sports and social club a members club in merley near the main manufacturing site in wimborne dorset which is used as the ground for merley cobham sports fc see alsoedit companies portal aerospace industry in the united kingdom cobham aviation services australia sargent fletcher cobham technical services  era technology ltd referencesedit  a b c annual report  pdf cobham plc retrieved  april    top  for  defensenewscom retrieved  march    a b obituary sir michael cobham the telegraph  april  retrieved  march    tarrant rushton  the secret airfield retrieved  march    aero history comcast   cobham buys stec corporation flying magazine  feb    cobham buys bae systems division the engineer uk  february    cobham to purchase sparta for m rf globalnet  january    tyco electronics announces agreement to sell its rf components and subsystem business to cobham plc press release tyco  may    cobham buys argotek pdf the engineer  may  retrieved  march    northrop grumman cobham team to resume work on us armys visx vehicular intercommunication system pdf defence aerospace  november  retrieved  march    parsons to buy systems unit from cobham for  million bloomberg  october  retrieved  march    cobham ups bid to secure thrane  thrane the telegraph  may  retrieved  march    cobham buys das provider axell wireless rcr wireless  may  retrieved  march    cobham pays £m to take control of helicopter firm that trained princes the telegraph  july  retrieved  march    cobham sells stec and chelton flight systems flying magazine retrieved  march    cobham acquires wireless communications company for